This is (IMHO) improved ConfigReader for python.
I never liked the mindset of the SML ConfigReader:

import ConfigReader
config = ConfigReader.ConfigReader()
config.read(configfile)
config.get(section, item)

So my reader does the same thing, this way:

import ReadConfig
config = ReadConfig.ReadConfig(configfile)
config.read(configfile)
config.section.item
